        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 14 at 4:38PM MDT by NWS Great Falls MT</headline>
        <description>At 437 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking gusty showers and isolated
thunderstorms across souther Beaverhead, Madison, and Gallatin
counties, moving northeast at 35 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Virginia City, Monida, Big Sky, Lakeview, Yellowstone Village,
Cameron, Snowline, Raynolds Pass, and Monida Pass.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building. Isolated
lightning strikes will be possible.</instruction>
